      <description>&lt;figure class=&#34;responsive-image&#34; style=&#34;margin: 2rem 0; text-align: center;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;picture&gt;&#xA;      &lt;source media=&#34;(max-width: 600px)&#34; srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/posts/quit_social_media/images/thumbnail_hu_6693ee2e57c0ca45.jpg&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;source media=&#34;(max-width: 900px)&#34; srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/posts/quit_social_media/images/thumbnail_hu_8799a0e91f3f14b0.jpg&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/posts/quit_social_media/images/thumbnail_hu_3939615de00873eb.jpg&#34; &#xA;           alt=&#34;Social media break&#34; &#xA;           loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;           style=&#34;max-width: 100%; height: auto; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/picture&gt;&lt;figcaption style=&#34;margin-top: 1rem; font-style: italic; color: #666; font-size: 0.9rem;&#34;&gt;Life after Instagram: quieter, calmer, better.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;tldr&#34;&gt;TL;DR&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Delete the app. Touch some grass. Text humans you actually like. Your brain will send you a thankyou card.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Two years later, I can confirm: you’re not missing out. You’re just finally living life without caring about what others are doing. And honestly? That feels insaneeeee in the best way.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
